Class Car

java.lang.Object
Car
public class Car
extends java.lang.Object
Car Class Containing methods for a Car.

This is a Class for a Car which contains methods needed for a car, like: accelerate(int), decelerate(int), turnOn(), turnOff(), stop(), drive(double),

      public Car​(java.lang.String make, java.lang.String model, int year, double price, double fuelEfficiency, double gasTank, double maxGasTank)
      Car constructor

      Constructs the Car. This is the Final Constructor that all the other constructors feed into.

      Parameters:
      make - Takes a String for the make of the Car.
      model - Takes a String for the model of the Car.
      year - Takes an int for the year of the Car.
      price - Takes a double for the price of the Car.
      fuelEfficiency - Takes a double for the fuel efficiency of the Car.
      gasTank - Takes a double for the fuel starting out in the gas tank of the Car.
      maxGasTank - Takes a double for the size of the gas tank in the Car.

    • drive

      public void drive​(double distance)
      Drives the Car Forward

      Drive the Car Forward in the direction that the car is pointing. This Direction can be changed with turnLeft() and turnRight()

      Parameters:
      distance - Takes a double for the distance the car will travel.

    • drive

      public void drive​(int seconds)
      Drives the Car Forward

      Drive the Car Forward in the direction that the car is pointing. This Direction can be changed with turnLeft() and turnRight() This method relies on the speed the car is currently going to determine distance covered during this time.

      Parameters:
      seconds - Takes an int for the time the car will travel.
